<%- include("partials/header") %>

<section class="page-shell">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-hero">
      <div class="page-copy">
        <p class="page-eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>Built as a scalable ecommerce foundation</h1>
        <p>
          This project is structured to give you a professional starting point for catalog,
          cart, checkout, payments, and admin workflows without dumping all of that logic into a single file.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="page-grid">
      <article class="info-card">
        <p class="page-eyebrow">Architecture</p>
        <h2>Clean separation of concerns</h2>
        <ul class="info-list">
          <li>Express routes, controllers, models, middleware, and config are separated.</li>
          <li>Product access now runs through a shared store layer for easier future expansion.</li>
          <li>The app can boot in fallback mode while MongoDB is offline.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="info-card">
        <p class="page-eyebrow">Commerce Ready</p>
        <h2>Prepared for the next features</h2>
        <ul class="info-list">
          <li>Session-based cart handling is already wired into the app flow.</li>
          <li>The folder structure is ready for checkout, payment, and admin modules.</li>
          <li>Sample product data makes the storefront usable before the live database is connected.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="info-card">
        <p class="page-eyebrow">Frontend</p>
        <h2>Designed to feel more premium</h2>
        <ul class="info-list">
          <li>The storefront now uses a stronger editorial visual direction.</li>
          <li>Home and products pages were upgraded to feel more like a real branded shop.</li>
          <li>These secondary pages now follow the same tone and spacing system.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include("partials/footer") %>
